Three months after Covid-19 broke out, Pankaj Shah was forced to shut down his tour operator business. In the second week of March, Kenya had announced the first Covid case, sending shudders across the business landscape.
A rampaging virus. Suspended international travel. Global gloom. Pankaj, 55, knew he would be out of business for many months. For the first time in 40 years, he was out of work. Few weeks later, the country went into lockdown.



