Nine months later, a multi-million shilling fund, hundreds of donors on board and hundreds of truckloads of food donations, Pankaj believes Covid-19 paved the way to his purpose in life.
His compassion, Pankaj said, was nurtured in 1988, after a brief interaction with Saint Mother Teresa during her visit in Kenya. Pankaj would later spend 100 days in Calcutta, India, volunteering at the home of the late Catholic nun.
When the Nation visited TeamPankaj offices, it had the air of a call centre. More than 10 assistants were busy making and answering phone calls from donors, community groups and leaders. Others were busy planning deliveries and doing clerical work, supervised by Pankaj.
This festive season, Pankaj is running a funds drive to collect money to buy food packages and other Christmas gifts for more than 15,000 families with autistic children and those with cerebral palsy.
Donations can be sent through M-Pesa till number 5074087 (Name: Serengeti). Buhari on Saturday urged security forces to arrest the gunmen. Rivalries in the ruling Jubilee Party play out in the Senate. Man wanted his mother to sell family land and give him the money. Their homes fell prey to Al-Shabaab gunmen swearing allegiance to the Islamic State group. They are seeking clearance with various regulatory agencies as the race to replace the late Justus Murunga intensifies.